[gentle music throughout]

01:32.458 --> 01:36.000
- [girl 1] <i>It's really hot out.</i>
- [girl 2] <i>It is hot out, but it's nice.</i>

01:36.000 --> 01:39.833
[girl 2] <i>I'm so excited to go to school.
I'm sad to leave this, though.</i>

01:39.833 --> 01:44.750
[girl 1] <i>Boys, boys, boys, boys...
Brand new boys.</i>

01:44.750 --> 01:47.625
[girl 2] <i>You'll probably find
some pretty boys in Santa Barbara.</i>

01:47.625 --> 01:51.083
<i>Yeah, I think I'm going to be on
the lookout for hot water polo players.</i>

01:51.083 --> 01:52.167
[girl 2] <i>Nice.</i>

01:52.750 --> 01:54.250
<i>I'm going to get something to drink.</i>

01:54.917 --> 01:58.958
<i>- Yeah, I'll go with you. I'm really hot.
- Yeah, let's go inside. I'm frying.</i>

01:58.958 --> 02:01.667
[news anchor] <i>And the debate continues
over the life of Terri Schiavo,</i>

02:01.667 --> 02:03.375
<i>who's right here in Tampa Bay...</i>

02:03.375 --> 02:06.625
[reporter] <i>Forty-one-year-old Schiavo
has had her feeding tube...</i>

02:06.625 --> 02:10.958
[Anna Nicole] <i>Tammy, Howard, Angie,
my make-up artist Lisa, my trainer...</i>

02:10.958 --> 02:13.375
<i>Even Sugar Pie was driving me crazy.</i>

02:13.792 --> 02:16.250
<i>Sugar Pie. Sugar Pie!</i>

02:16.250 --> 02:18.583
S <i>ugar Pie! Sugar Pie.</i>

02:20.833 --> 02:24.333
Oh, God, I can't stand
looking at that poor woman.

02:26.208 --> 02:28.708
Hey. Hi.

02:30.708 --> 02:33.125
[tv show host] <i>Let's give it up
for Anna Nicole Smith.</i>

02:33.125 --> 02:36.583
My head is killing me,
and this isn't helping.

02:39.208 --> 02:41.208
[Anna Nicole] <i>I was so embarrassed, and...</i>

02:43.375 --> 02:45.083
I got you nachos.

02:49.750 --> 02:52.833
- [dog barks]
- [Anna Nicole] <i>Sugar Pie! Shut up...</i>

02:55.625 --> 02:58.833
- Well, did you give him his shot?
- Yes, I did.

02:59.833 --> 03:01.500
Did you vacuum?

03:01.500 --> 03:03.208
- Yeah.
- Doesn't look like it.

03:03.208 --> 03:05.292
'Cause the carpet's a thousand years old.

03:09.125 --> 03:11.708
God, this place really has
turned into a shit hole.

03:17.125 --> 03:19.125
I'm going to need your help
with him in the morning.

03:19.500 --> 03:20.708
I can't. I'll miss the van.

03:21.292 --> 03:24.208
Oh, Doris, it's a big day.
You don't have to go to school.

03:24.208 --> 03:25.583
[Doris] But I want to go.

03:26.333 --> 03:29.250
- You'll be late and I'll write you a note.
- No, please, Mom.

03:29.250 --> 03:32.000
I'll have to interrupt class
and everyone looks at me...

03:32.000 --> 03:33.083
It's really embarrassing.

03:33.083 --> 03:35.833
Oh it's really embarrassing. Oh, well...

03:35.833 --> 03:38.500
Oh, well, then I guess I'll just have to
drop your brother off by myself,

03:38.500 --> 03:40.000
because God forbid,
you should be embarrassed.

03:40.000 --> 03:41.458
Okay, fine. I'll come. Forget it.

03:41.458 --> 03:43.167
No? Oh, are you sure?

03:43.167 --> 03:46.125
You sure? Because I wouldn't want you
to blush in front of your friends.

03:46.125 --> 03:49.125
I don't have any friends.
And fine, I said forget it.

03:53.000 --> 03:55.375
[Anna Nicole] <i>Sugar Pie,
shut the</i> [bleep] <i>up.</i>

03:58.625 --> 04:02.708
- [grunting]
- [Mom] Okay. One, two, three. Go.

04:03.792 --> 04:05.083
[Mom] Oh, my God. Okay.

04:05.083 --> 04:07.125
- [Mom] Lift him up.
- [Doris] I'm trying.

04:07.125 --> 04:08.375
Come on.

04:08.750 --> 04:10.333
[vehicle brakes]

04:12.000 --> 04:14.000
I'm taking her today.

04:14.833 --> 04:16.250
You can go.

04:20.792 --> 04:21.792
[Mom] What is he? Deaf?

04:21.792 --> 04:23.875
Mom, stop yelling.
He obviously can't hear you.

04:23.875 --> 04:24.958
Okay.

04:26.875 --> 04:28.167
Hello?

04:28.542 --> 04:31.625
I'm taking her. You can go!

04:32.375 --> 04:34.625
- Drive away!
- Mom, stop yelling.

04:34.625 --> 04:36.292
Everyone is staring at us.

04:36.667 --> 04:40.458
[Mom] Okay, lift his upper body.
Up, here we go.

04:41.625 --> 04:43.417
There we go. That's good.

04:43.417 --> 04:45.708
All right, sweetheart. Sorry.

04:45.708 --> 04:47.042
I'm so sorry.

04:47.042 --> 04:48.417
Can I drive?

04:48.417 --> 04:50.292
[Mom] What? No, no, no, no.
We don't have time.

04:50.292 --> 04:52.375
- Come on, you never let me--
- Doris!

04:52.375 --> 04:54.458
Please, not today.

04:56.833 --> 04:57.833
Okay.

05:00.250 --> 05:01.250
All right.

05:02.667 --> 05:04.875
[Mom] [stammering] Get in the back!

05:05.375 --> 05:07.042
- What?
- The latch has been screwy.

05:07.042 --> 05:08.792
You got to make sure
his chair doesn't fall out.

05:08.792 --> 05:10.250
My hair is gonna go nuts.

05:11.958 --> 05:13.083
Your hair?

05:33.042 --> 05:34.333
[Mom] Goddamn piece of crap.

05:47.708 --> 05:49.208
For fuck's sake.

05:50.417 --> 05:52.833
[engine revs]

05:53.208 --> 05:56.000
[gentle music throughout]

06:31.250 --> 06:32.750
[horn honks]

06:36.083 --> 06:38.583
[crowd chattering]

06:51.208 --> 06:55.208
Excuse me. If you don't mind
I just need to check your bags.

06:56.542 --> 06:57.542
Why?

06:57.542 --> 06:59.708
[security guard] Unfortunately,
the staff gets a lot of threats

06:59.708 --> 07:01.792
since Mrs. Schiavo got here.

07:01.792 --> 07:04.542
[Mom] So you think while I'm dropping
my son off, I'm going to kill someone?

07:04.542 --> 07:06.333
[Doris] Just let her check your bags.

07:06.333 --> 07:10.292
Hi, there. Is everything okay?
I'm Mia, the Director of Nursing.

07:10.292 --> 07:12.833
- You're the Director? How old are you?
- Mom!

07:12.833 --> 07:14.792
- It's okay.
- What? It's just a question.

07:14.792 --> 07:17.750
How old are you?
'Cause you do. You look young.

07:17.750 --> 07:19.542
[Mia] I actually get that a lot.

07:22.167 --> 07:24.000
Don't worry about your bags.

07:24.000 --> 07:26.083
If you both want to follow me,
I can check you in.

07:27.750 --> 07:28.833
This way.

07:30.375 --> 07:33.292
[crowd shouting outside]

07:38.250 --> 07:39.667
[light scrubbing]

07:39.667 --> 07:42.417
[Mom] I can't believe that teenager
just shoved us in here.

07:43.792 --> 07:46.000
Look at this. Look!

07:46.000 --> 07:47.542
Look at this.

07:48.042 --> 07:51.125
I'm so sorry, honey.
I'm going to clean this place up.

07:51.125 --> 07:53.333
This room is way cleaner than our house.

07:53.958 --> 07:55.208
I don't know if this...

07:57.208 --> 07:58.667
Do you think this is
the right place for him?

07:58.667 --> 08:00.333
I just-- I'm not so sure.

08:00.333 --> 08:02.500
You'd say that about any place.

08:02.500 --> 08:04.875
Are you not at all upset about this?

08:06.417 --> 08:08.500
This is it, Doris.

08:08.500 --> 08:11.125
This filthy box is where
your brother's going to die.

08:11.125 --> 08:12.792
Of course I'm upset.

08:14.083 --> 08:15.833
Can we go soon? I'm already really late.

08:15.833 --> 08:20.583
You know, you could just try and think
about someone other than yourself.

08:20.583 --> 08:22.042
You might like it.

08:22.042 --> 08:23.583
Brad and Jen just broke up.

08:23.583 --> 08:24.833
Right now I'm thinking about them.

08:24.833 --> 08:27.458
Oh, they did?

08:30.000 --> 08:31.000
I knew they would.

08:31.000 --> 08:32.875
The second they got married.
What did I say?

08:32.875 --> 08:34.375
- He's too handsome.
-"He's too handsome."

08:34.792 --> 08:36.542
The handsome ones never stay.

08:39.292 --> 08:40.542
Like your brother.

08:42.708 --> 08:44.667
Too handsome for this world.

08:45.875 --> 08:47.333
Can we go now, please?

08:49.500 --> 08:55.958
[gentle music plays]

08:58.583 --> 09:01.333
Welcome back, Doris. Thank you.

09:05.125 --> 09:08.333
[student 1] Dude, she said it was a
one-time thing, like, I don't know.

09:08.333 --> 09:09.625
Oh, my gosh.

09:09.625 --> 09:12.208
You seriously think
Cody's hooking up with Tiffany?

09:12.208 --> 09:15.208
I know for a fact he did
and good riddance.

09:15.208 --> 09:17.417
Let her keep his dirty dick.

09:17.417 --> 09:18.917
[student 2] He is not
hooking up with Tiffany.

09:18.917 --> 09:21.167
[student 1] Bullshit.
Tiffany told me herself.

09:21.167 --> 09:24.000
She showed me a hickey.
It was shaped like Cody's dirty mouth.

09:24.000 --> 09:25.833
[student 2] Okay, well,
y'all should come over later.

09:25.833 --> 09:28.125
Okay, we're gonna grill by the pool
and Cody will be there,

09:28.125 --> 09:29.625
so you can just ask him yourself.

09:29.625 --> 09:31.375
Okay. Cody's going to be there?

09:31.375 --> 09:35.083
Yes, you best believe my ass will be there
'cause I'm done with these rumors.

09:35.083 --> 09:37.750
[teacher] Okay. Sounds like
most of us are done with the assignment.

09:39.667 --> 09:43.042
So let's talk about being naked in public.

09:44.875 --> 09:46.625
Is that an ethics question?

09:47.708 --> 09:48.708
Yes, Adam.

09:48.708 --> 09:51.292
Well, that depends on
the laws of the land.

09:51.292 --> 09:52.458
[teacher] Exactly.

09:52.458 --> 09:57.167
Banning public nudity is a rule
of a particular society, our society,

09:58.000 --> 09:59.250
especially this classroom.

10:00.250 --> 10:02.375
But what about Christian ethics?

10:02.375 --> 10:04.458
How do they differ
from the law of the land?

10:04.458 --> 10:06.375
[school bell rings]

10:06.917 --> 10:10.500
[teacher] Whoa, what's your hurry?
Am I that boring?

10:13.833 --> 10:15.917
Oh, excuse me.

10:15.917 --> 10:17.417
Yeah, okay.

10:18.208 --> 10:19.583
[high-pitched sustained beep]

10:19.583 --> 10:23.292
[Mom] Do you hear it? It's like...
[screeches]

10:24.042 --> 10:26.000
It's got to be driving him insane.

10:27.292 --> 10:30.375
Do not worry, honey.
I'm going to fix this.

10:30.375 --> 10:31.625
[Doris] I doubt he hears it.

10:31.625 --> 10:33.625
Here, get up. I need your chair.

10:33.625 --> 10:35.958
[beep continues]

10:35.958 --> 10:38.792
Of course-- I told that robot
at the front desk,

10:38.792 --> 10:40.292
but of course she didn't do anything.

10:40.292 --> 10:42.625
Mia? You seriously don't like her?

10:42.625 --> 10:44.542
She's, like, the nicest person
I've ever met.

10:44.542 --> 10:49.417
Yeah, well, she's a toddler.
She just goes around smiling.

10:49.417 --> 10:52.208
You shouldn't walk around grinning
if your job is watching people die,

10:52.208 --> 10:55.042
and your brother is stuck here
with this horrible noise.

10:55.042 --> 10:56.375
Here.

10:56.875 --> 10:59.875
Help me up,
I'm gonna stick my head up here.

11:00.333 --> 11:02.042
See what the fuck is going on.

11:02.042 --> 11:03.125
Mom!

11:03.125 --> 11:06.958
For the love of God, Doris,
come over here.

11:06.958 --> 11:09.167
- You're going to fall.
- Well, then you make sure I don't.

11:10.375 --> 11:12.125
[Doris] Can you please just hurry up?

11:12.125 --> 11:13.667
[Mom] Quiet. I can't hear it
when you're talking?

11:13.667 --> 11:17.500
- Everything okay in here?
- No, no, it is not okay in here.

11:17.500 --> 11:21.125
My son is a prisoner here
and he's been tortured by that noise.

11:21.125 --> 11:24.917
- There's barely a noise.
- [screeches]

11:24.917 --> 11:26.417
[Mom] You don't hear that?

11:28.292 --> 11:31.083
Whatever. I'm sorry about her.

11:31.625 --> 11:32.958
She's a lunatic.

11:38.625 --> 11:39.833
[Mom] Thank you.

11:42.583 --> 11:46.458
[crowd chatters]

11:46.917 --> 11:49.125
