11:57.833 --> 12:01.083
<i>♪ Wake the fuck up
'cause it's been too long ♪</i>

12:01.083 --> 12:03.708
<i>♪ Say wait a minute,
Queen what's your name? ♪</i>

12:03.708 --> 12:07.750
<i>♪ I be that gypsy flippin' life game
from the right brain ♪</i>

12:07.750 --> 12:09.917
<i>♪ Ascension maintained ♪</i>

12:09.917 --> 12:12.458
<i>♪ Rolling through like a burning flame ♪</i>

12:12.458 --> 12:15.458
<i>♪ Like a super nova star ♪</i>

12:15.458 --> 12:18.208
<i>♪ She be the light when they in the dark ♪</i>

12:18.208 --> 12:19.667
<i>♪ Morning ♪</i>

12:20.208 --> 12:24.125
<i>♪ The moon pass the sun
four constellations start forming ♪</i>

12:24.125 --> 12:27.000
<i>♪ Across up in the sky ♪</i>

12:27.000 --> 12:29.708
<i>♪ But everybody wanna ask me why ♪</i>

12:29.708 --> 12:35.708
<i>♪ What good do your words do
if they can't understand you? ♪</i>

12:35.708 --> 12:41.083
<i>♪ Don't go talkin' that shit Badu, Badu ♪</i>

12:41.083 --> 12:44.333
<i>♪ Don't go talkin' that shit Badu... ♪</i>

12:44.333 --> 12:47.208
[cashier] Cheeseburger, fries
and a chocolate shake,

12:47.208 --> 12:48.958
That's 9.68.

12:51.208 --> 12:53.667
Oh, forget the shake.

12:55.333 --> 12:59.125
Keep the shake. I got it.
Add fish and chips for me.

13:00.958 --> 13:04.167
Thank you. That's so nice of you
but you really don't...

13:04.167 --> 13:07.667
No, no, no buts. You take the food,
you're skinny as a rail.

13:07.667 --> 13:10.375
I bet you can't even see your shadow.

13:11.625 --> 13:16.125
- Okay, well, thank you again.
- Yup. Yup, yup.

13:22.958 --> 13:25.833
Well, mind if I join?

13:27.125 --> 13:28.125
Yeah.

13:28.125 --> 13:33.458
I mean, no, no, I don't mind if...
Yeah, you can sit here, if you want.

13:38.958 --> 13:42.792
I think I saw you over at that
executional chamber.

13:43.708 --> 13:44.917
Suncoast?

13:45.292 --> 13:48.083
- [man] Yeah.
- [Doris] Yeah. My brother's living there.

13:48.458 --> 13:50.292
Or... dying there.

13:50.292 --> 13:52.333
Oh, I'm so sorry.

13:52.708 --> 13:55.792
Well, I'll pray for his recovery.

13:55.792 --> 13:57.042
Oh, please don't.

13:58.917 --> 14:01.917
I just mean he has brain cancer

14:01.917 --> 14:06.000
and he's blind and he can't walk,
and he hasn't talked in years.

14:06.000 --> 14:08.625
I mean, like, his brain
just doesn't really function anymore.

14:09.208 --> 14:12.583
Like, he still eats on his own,
but not for long.

14:12.583 --> 14:17.042
So if he survived, I just...
don't think he'd be happy.

14:18.208 --> 14:19.208
Still...

14:20.208 --> 14:22.375
every life is precious.

14:26.583 --> 14:31.208
I do not know why I just laughed.
It's obviously not funny.

14:32.208 --> 14:33.208
Sorry,

14:33.208 --> 14:35.958
I haven't, like, talked to
another person in a long time.

14:37.167 --> 14:40.542
I've just been taking care of my brother
and haven't had time to really, like,

14:40.542 --> 14:42.167
talk to anyone.

14:42.625 --> 14:47.958
Well, maybe you shouldn't start now
'cause you're pretty bad at it.

14:47.958 --> 14:49.833
[Doris laughs softly]

14:49.833 --> 14:52.292
- [man] Oh, yay.
- [Doris] Thank you.

14:57.833 --> 15:00.417
- Not a fan?
- Oh, sorry.

15:00.417 --> 15:02.708
Just the smell of seafood
kinda grosses me out.

15:02.708 --> 15:05.917
Well, maybe you haven't smelled
the right seafood.

15:05.917 --> 15:08.042
- Maybe not.
- No, definitely not.

15:08.042 --> 15:11.083
Have you been to West Palm Beach?

15:11.083 --> 15:13.542
- No.
- Wooh whee!

15:13.542 --> 15:15.208
You're gonna love West Palm Beach.

15:15.208 --> 15:18.917
Go to Captain Joe's.
Best fish tacos in the world.

15:18.917 --> 15:21.833
- Grouper. You'll love it.
- I doubt it.

15:25.125 --> 15:27.167
My wife was obsessed with them.

15:30.208 --> 15:31.792
She passed away.

15:33.750 --> 15:35.000
I'm sorry.

15:35.625 --> 15:36.792
Me too.

15:37.375 --> 15:40.625
My dad died.
He had a heart attack when I was three.

15:41.917 --> 15:45.750
Christ, it ain't a competition.
But if it was, you'd be winning.

15:48.208 --> 15:51.792
Hey, yeah. Paul.

15:51.792 --> 15:54.125
- Doris.
- Doris?

15:54.125 --> 15:56.208
Really? Old lady's name.

15:56.208 --> 15:57.792
It was my grandma's name.

15:57.792 --> 15:59.875
- Oh.
- She died the day I was born.

16:00.625 --> 16:03.375
My God. Is there any conversation with you

16:03.375 --> 16:05.833
that it's not, like,
thoroughly depressing?

16:07.250 --> 16:10.042
Basically, everyone in my family is dead,
except my mom.

16:10.042 --> 16:12.125
But I sometimes kind of wish she was.

16:12.750 --> 16:13.875
Don't say that.

16:14.625 --> 16:17.750
- I'm-- I'm kidding.
- Yeah, well, that's not funny.

16:18.125 --> 16:21.083
Every life is precious,
including your mother's.

16:21.083 --> 16:23.792
No one has ever called my mom precious.

16:25.458 --> 16:26.542
Oh, God.

16:30.333 --> 16:32.458
Jesus, Doris.

16:32.458 --> 16:35.250
I've been looking everywhere for you.
What? You just walk off?

16:35.250 --> 16:36.667
You don't answer your phone.

16:36.667 --> 16:39.042
- Hello?
- Mom, this is Paul.

16:40.042 --> 16:41.125
Nice to meet you.

16:43.125 --> 16:44.625
- Hi.
- Hi.

16:45.042 --> 16:47.625
Let's go. I'm gonna be late for work.

16:49.792 --> 16:52.667
See? Isn't she precious?
It was nice meeting you.

16:52.667 --> 16:54.667
- Nice to meet you.
- Let's go, let's go, let's go...

16:54.667 --> 16:57.000
- Can I drive?
- No. I just said I'm late.

17:00.250 --> 17:03.208
[television news chatter]

17:04.708 --> 17:05.708
[news anchor] <i>...as Hurricane Zeta</i>

17:05.708 --> 17:08.292
<i>rips through
the Keys and up the Gulf of Mexico.</i>

17:09.000 --> 17:12.625
<i>Fill up those gas tanks and generators
this could be a long weekend.</i>

17:13.292 --> 17:15.417
This storm could be a real bitch.

17:18.083 --> 17:19.375
You should board up the windows.

17:19.958 --> 17:22.542
[news anchor] <i>It's the first time
Jacksonville has ever hosted</i>

17:22.542 --> 17:25.250
<i>a Super Bowl at the Alltel Stadium...</i>

17:25.250 --> 17:27.042
I think I should start
sleeping at Suncoast

17:27.042 --> 17:28.917
so your brother doesn't get too lonely.

17:28.917 --> 17:31.042
[news anchor] <i>...in an attempt to avoid
repeating a controversial incident...</i>

17:31.042 --> 17:32.250
But...

17:33.958 --> 17:35.417
then I'll be alone.

17:37.375 --> 17:39.375
You'll be in your own home.

17:40.833 --> 17:43.833
He's in a new place,
surrounded by strangers.

17:43.833 --> 17:45.583
- But I don't--
- You know, Doris...

17:47.125 --> 17:49.417
When you have your own kids,
you'll understand.

17:50.042 --> 17:53.417
I just can't stand the idea of him
in that place by himself.

17:53.958 --> 17:55.417
He's my child.

17:55.417 --> 17:57.875
When he's in pain, I'm in pain.

17:58.917 --> 18:00.208
I'm your child, too.

18:00.208 --> 18:02.083
- [Mom] For God's sake.
- [Doris] What about my pain?

18:02.083 --> 18:03.292
Give me a break.

18:03.292 --> 18:05.042
What if the storm gets really bad?

18:05.042 --> 18:07.583
And what if there's a blackout?
We don't have a generator.

18:07.583 --> 18:09.667
[Mom] Please, just will you think
about your brother?

18:10.125 --> 18:13.208
He's trapped in his own body.
He can't move, he can't see...

18:13.208 --> 18:15.250
You're worried about using
a flashlight for one night?

18:15.250 --> 18:17.000
I'm going to be sleeping
on a cot for weeks.

18:17.000 --> 18:18.292
I said, fine.

18:23.333 --> 18:26.792
[teacher] And because it is legal
in all 50 states, is it ethical?

18:27.792 --> 18:31.958
Do we blindly accept the ethics
of our government as our own?

18:31.958 --> 18:33.042
No.

18:33.958 --> 18:36.708
And we know abortion is wrong
because the Bible says it is.

18:37.250 --> 18:38.792
[teacher] That's actually not true, Adam.

18:38.792 --> 18:41.083
There is no
explicit prohibition of abortion

18:41.083 --> 18:43.792
in either the Old or the New Testament.

18:43.792 --> 18:46.625
Okay, well, I still think it's wrong.

18:47.167 --> 18:48.917
Well, I think you're an idiot.

18:49.417 --> 18:51.708
[teacher] Ah, good. A debate.

18:52.375 --> 18:55.208
Why don't both of you come in on Monday
with your prepared arguments?

18:55.208 --> 18:56.375
Love it.

18:57.208 --> 18:58.958
[student 1] You should have
kept your mouth shut.

18:58.958 --> 19:01.000
I'm a feminist, and I won't be silenced.

19:01.000 --> 19:02.083
[cellphone buzzes]

19:02.208 --> 19:04.833
[teacher] Let's talk about bioethics...

19:05.875 --> 19:08.917
Well, Kyle's dad found out
he was going to throw a hurricane party.

19:08.917 --> 19:10.667
Now his parents aren't going to evacuate.

19:10.667 --> 19:13.208
What? That freakin' sucks balls.

19:13.208 --> 19:15.042
Well, we have to go somewhere

19:15.042 --> 19:18.583
because I already told my parents
I'm going on an overnight field trip.

19:20.542 --> 19:23.250
[student 3] Seriously, though,
I really want to go out. Please?

19:23.250 --> 19:24.625
[student 1] Can we go to Tara's?

19:24.625 --> 19:27.167
- [student 3] Didn't she get her own place?
- [student 2] She got evicted.

19:27.167 --> 19:29.042
- [student 1] Of course she did.
- [student 2] Yeah.

19:29.042 --> 19:32.167
[student 2] Marcus said he might get a keg
and go under the causeway.

19:32.167 --> 19:34.708
Waves are going to be so big,
he's going to bail.

19:34.708 --> 19:38.333
- We can go to the movies.
- Yeah, right after I kill myself.

19:39.958 --> 19:41.250
You can come to my house.

19:46.750 --> 19:50.958
I mean, my mom won't be there,
and you can do whatever you want.

19:50.958 --> 19:53.167
But if not, it's cool.

19:53.625 --> 19:55.750
I just thought
if you needed a place to party,

19:55.750 --> 20:01.000
you could totally come over.
Or whatever you want. It's chill.

20:01.792 --> 20:04.167
Yeah. Super chill.

20:04.833 --> 20:07.208
[student 2] So there's, like, no adults?

20:07.208 --> 20:11.042
- Can we roll?
- Sure. Whatever you want.

20:11.667 --> 20:17.333
Wait. Guys, this is, like, so dope.
Oh, my God, I have to tell everybody.

20:18.750 --> 20:20.250
But who are you?

20:20.250 --> 20:22.667
Yeah, yeah. What's your name?

20:22.667 --> 20:24.125
Doris.

20:24.125 --> 20:26.500
Cool. Nate.

20:26.500 --> 20:28.917
Yeah, cool.

20:28.917 --> 20:30.500
- Laci.
- Brittany.

20:30.500 --> 20:32.417
Cool. Doris.

20:33.375 --> 20:34.375
Cool.

20:35.583 --> 20:40.833
[angsty rock music plays]

20:49.333 --> 20:52.375
<i>♪ Where I come from isn't all that great ♪</i>

20:52.375 --> 20:55.125
<i>♪ My automobile is a piece of crap ♪</i>

20:55.125 --> 20:57.542
<i>♪ My fashion sense is a little wack ♪</i>

20:57.875 --> 21:00.542
<i>♪ And my friends
are just as screwy as me ♪</i>

21:00.542 --> 21:03.500
<i>♪ I didn't go to boarding schools ♪</i>

21:03.500 --> 21:06.125
<i>♪ Preppy girls never looked at me ♪</i>

21:06.125 --> 21:11.042
<i>♪ Why should they? I ain't nobody
Got nothing in my pocket ♪</i>

21:11.042 --> 21:13.667
<i>♪ Beverly Hills ♪</i>

21:13.667 --> 21:17.000
<i>♪ That's where I want to be ♪</i>

21:17.000 --> 21:19.083
<i>♪ Gimme gimme, gimme gimme ♪</i>

21:19.083 --> 21:21.750
<i>♪ Livin' in Beverly Hills ♪</i>

21:21.750 --> 21:24.250
<i>♪ Beverly Hills ♪</i>

21:24.250 --> 21:27.958
<i>♪ Rollin' like a celebrity ♪</i>

21:28.792 --> 21:30.792
- Hi.
- Hey.

21:31.833 --> 21:36.250
Oh, your house is so cute.

21:36.250 --> 21:38.333
[Brittany] It's super...

21:39.542 --> 21:41.833
homey and, like...

21:43.167 --> 21:45.417
- [Brittany] very unique.
- [Megan] Yeah.

21:45.417 --> 21:48.083
[Megan] Everyone says
this neighborhood is scary,

21:48.083 --> 21:52.750
but, like, when you're in it,
it's like, not that scary.

21:53.750 --> 21:55.000
Thank you.

21:55.375 --> 21:57.583
Sorta smells like piss in here.

21:58.125 --> 22:03.417
Oh, that's probably from my cat

22:04.125 --> 22:06.875
who's just running around here somewhere.

22:09.375 --> 22:10.375
I have a cat.

22:11.917 --> 22:15.375
[loud party music plays]

22:20.833 --> 22:22.083
Cheers.

22:26.625 --> 22:28.875
[loud rave music]

22:38.167 --> 22:40.583
[music thumps]

22:57.417 --> 22:59.500
[music, party chatter]

23:04.208 --> 23:05.292
Want one?

23:06.333 --> 23:07.500
Oh.

23:07.500 --> 23:11.583
Uh, uh... no. Thank you.

23:14.917 --> 23:18.375
[loud music and chatter continues]

23:18.500 --> 23:20.875
[Doris] So you have a pool?

23:21.542 --> 23:23.333
- Huh?
- In class.

23:23.333 --> 23:25.125
I heard you say you have a pool.

23:26.292 --> 23:28.625
Oh, yeah. Yeah, I do.

23:34.167 --> 23:37.083
So, what do your parents do?

23:38.167 --> 23:40.083
What do you mean? Like their jobs?

23:41.042 --> 23:42.208
Never mind.

23:43.500 --> 23:46.083
- My mom has a parrot.
- Really?

23:46.083 --> 23:47.583
[Nate] Yeah. Yeah, she got it to talk.

23:47.583 --> 23:49.667
She got it to say...

23:50.250 --> 23:51.417
[imitating a parrot] "I love you, Nate."

23:51.417 --> 23:52.583
[laughs]

23:52.583 --> 23:54.708
Yeah, it was kind of weird at first,

23:54.708 --> 23:56.875
but now I sort of, like,
look forward to it.

23:57.833 --> 23:59.833
That's really sweet.

24:00.625 --> 24:02.042
Yeah. Yeah.

24:06.583 --> 24:11.083
- [loud music]
- [thunder rolling]

24:12.208 --> 24:15.708
[indistinct chatter]

24:16.292 --> 24:20.917
[Brittany] Doris, come sit. Come sit.
Come here. Come on.

24:20.917 --> 24:25.333
This house is amazing.

24:25.333 --> 24:28.542
It's so... small.

24:29.250 --> 24:33.542
It's like a doll house. It's incredible.

24:33.542 --> 24:35.792
You're so beautiful.

24:35.792 --> 24:38.000
- [Doris] No.
- [Laci] No, no, you are.

24:38.000 --> 24:41.125
[Laci] And you're just, like, so natural.

24:41.125 --> 24:44.875
And your nose is just, like, so real.

24:44.875 --> 24:46.583
[Brittany] Beyond real.

24:47.250 --> 24:50.375
You're like this... lion

24:50.375 --> 24:53.083
- Yes!
- ...with your wild hair.

24:53.500 --> 24:55.833
[Laci] Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

24:55.833 --> 24:57.708
- She's a lion.
- She's a lion.

24:58.250 --> 25:00.833
- Roar!
- Roar!

25:00.833 --> 25:02.542
[both] Roar!

25:02.542 --> 25:04.208
Roar with us.

25:04.208 --> 25:06.083
[all] Roar.

25:06.083 --> 25:07.542
[Both] Yeah!

25:08.083 --> 25:10.083
[birds chirping]

25:15.333 --> 25:18.625
[distant crowd chanting]

25:37.958 --> 25:41.250
[somber music]

26:48.250 --> 26:51.583
- Good morning.
- Morning.

26:54.042 --> 26:58.750
You're here early.
We don't usually get visitors this early.

27:00.667 --> 27:03.292
Well, I slept here last night.

27:04.125 --> 27:08.542
- My son is here.
- Well, he's lucky to have you.

27:10.917 --> 27:14.417
Well... what about you?

27:16.000 --> 27:18.833
Does your family visit? I mean, I hope so.

27:19.250 --> 27:22.750
I can't imagine only having
these fake nurses to talk to.

27:22.750 --> 27:24.833
No, I'm not.

27:26.542 --> 27:29.875
I'm not a patient. I work here.

27:32.583 --> 27:34.500
Oh, Jesus Christ.

27:34.500 --> 27:36.375
Oh, I thought because...

27:36.375 --> 27:38.458
Oh, look, that-- That is.

27:38.458 --> 27:41.333
- [woman] No, I'm not dying.
- [Mom] That's my mistake.

27:41.333 --> 27:43.083
I guess I should have
put on lipstick this morning.

27:43.083 --> 27:47.625
No, I am so sorry.
That was a dumbass thing to say.

27:47.625 --> 27:48.833
It's okay.

27:49.917 --> 27:53.458
I'm Sue. I'm the grief counselor here.

27:54.167 --> 27:58.333
And I'm available to talk
if you ever want to.

27:59.750 --> 28:00.958
Oh.

28:02.917 --> 28:05.667
Oh, my son isn't dead,
so I'm not really grieving yet.

28:06.750 --> 28:11.958
[Sue] Okay, well...
I'm here if you change your mind.

28:12.083 --> 28:13.542
Okay.

28:17.708 --> 28:19.917
[Mom] Well, I should get back...

28:19.917 --> 28:21.958
- Sure. Yeah.
- ...to...

28:24.542 --> 28:25.542
Yeah.

28:36.500 --> 28:37.625
Shit.

28:43.958 --> 28:47.667
Hey, what are you doing with that?

28:48.750 --> 28:53.292
I was just... moving it out of the way,

28:53.292 --> 28:55.958
'cause we don't need any more, right?

28:58.500 --> 28:59.667
No, I guess not.

29:03.333 --> 29:04.375
How was the storm?

29:05.667 --> 29:08.625
Not bad. Sort of fun, actually.

29:09.208 --> 29:10.292
Fun?

29:10.625 --> 29:15.792
[Doris] No, I didn't mean fun.
I didn't have fun because I was alone.

29:15.792 --> 29:20.667
So... There was a blackout,
and I lit some candles.

29:20.667 --> 29:23.625
And... candles are fun.

29:27.792 --> 29:28.917
You're being weird.

29:29.542 --> 29:31.917
What? No, I'm not.

29:41.583 --> 29:44.167
[Mom] It won't kill you to spend
a few hours with your brother.

29:44.167 --> 29:49.042
But I spent six years with him,
and he has nurses taking care of him now.

29:51.000 --> 29:52.208
Get out of the truck.

29:52.792 --> 29:55.042
Excuse me, ma'am.

29:55.042 --> 29:57.667
I'm sorry, but we need to check
the back of your vehicle.

29:58.708 --> 29:59.875
For what?

30:00.500 --> 30:03.375
[officer] Frankly, we received
a bomb threat yesterday,

30:03.375 --> 30:05.458
and we're taking it pretty seriously.

30:06.125 --> 30:09.958
Everyone in there is about to die anyway.
Who would waste a bomb on that place?

30:09.958 --> 30:12.583
Ignore her. Please, just do
whatever you need to do.

30:15.333 --> 30:16.708
It's unbelievable.

30:20.625 --> 30:23.417
What's in the back there, ma'am?

30:28.542 --> 30:34.000
Well, Officer... that is an oxygen tank.

30:35.542 --> 30:38.375
Because my son's cancer
spread to his lungs.

30:39.958 --> 30:41.208
[Mom] Is that illegal?

30:43.083 --> 30:44.083
Get out.

30:45.917 --> 30:48.167
I'm not staying any way,
I've got to get to work.

30:49.000 --> 30:53.333
At the bomb factory...
where I make hospice bombs.

31:01.875 --> 31:06.292
[gentle music]

31:24.333 --> 31:25.625
Can I have one?

31:27.292 --> 31:28.500
How old are you?

31:29.250 --> 31:31.583
Fine. I'll just go buy some.

31:32.333 --> 31:35.375
You're so full of shit
your eyes are turning brown.

31:35.375 --> 31:38.458
- My eyes are brown.
- Exactly.

31:40.708 --> 31:42.792
You go to Clearwater Christian?

31:44.208 --> 31:45.333
How do you know that?

31:46.583 --> 31:48.792
I know everything about you, Doris.

31:53.125 --> 31:54.958
I'm kidding. It's on your shirt.

31:55.750 --> 31:59.417
- Oh.
- Are you Christian?

32:03.167 --> 32:05.458
No, not exactly.

32:05.458 --> 32:07.500
My mom actually thinks
religion is bullshit.

32:07.500 --> 32:08.792
No offense.

32:08.792 --> 32:11.083
She just didn't want me
going to the public school

32:11.083 --> 32:13.292
after some kid shot a math teacher.

32:13.292 --> 32:15.708
So she has to work all the time
to pay my tuition.

32:15.708 --> 32:17.542
She never shuts up about it.

32:18.750 --> 32:20.000
She's a good mom.

32:20.500 --> 32:23.000
Um... no.

32:23.542 --> 32:26.083
To my brother, maybe, but not to me.

32:27.375 --> 32:30.125
[Paul] You know,
Terri went to Catholic school.

32:30.125 --> 32:31.833
[Doris] How do you know?

32:32.667 --> 32:35.167
- [Paul] Just do.
- [Doris] Do you know her?

32:36.750 --> 32:39.917
- Well, no. I don't know her personally.
- What do you mean?

32:41.250 --> 32:43.167
I don't know her.

32:43.167 --> 32:46.958
But when I found out
that her psychotic husband

32:46.958 --> 32:51.667
was trying to murder her,
I had to come here and do something.

32:51.667 --> 32:56.458
Murder her? But...
You know, she's basically already dead.

32:57.625 --> 32:59.625
She's as alive as you are.

33:01.042 --> 33:03.417
And what if it was you
in there instead of her?

33:06.375 --> 33:10.708
Bottom line is, her husband
didn't want to take care of her anymore.

33:12.000 --> 33:13.667
Honestly, I get that.

33:14.917 --> 33:18.208
It's really hard
taking care of sick people.

33:19.375 --> 33:20.667
Sometimes you need a break.

33:22.167 --> 33:23.792
[Paul] Are you enjoying your break?

33:26.875 --> 33:29.375
I mean, this is going to sound horrible,

33:30.208 --> 33:32.458
but... yeah.

33:36.000 --> 33:39.125
Once your brother's gone, he's gone...

33:40.500 --> 33:44.667
and he is never coming back.
And you will miss taking care of him.

33:44.667 --> 33:47.458
- [Doris] No, I won't.
- [Paul] You will.

33:48.042 --> 33:52.000
[Paul] You'll miss everything.
All the good, all the bad...

33:52.708 --> 33:54.333
Hell, especially the bad.

33:55.333 --> 34:01.000
I'd give anything to hear my wife yell
at me for letting the mosquitoes inside.

34:03.750 --> 34:05.750
Just talk to her, you know?

34:08.625 --> 34:11.583
Well, I haven't talked
to my brother in years.

34:11.583 --> 34:13.667
He's not really aware.

34:14.833 --> 34:16.583
[Paul] Well, you should talk to him.

34:16.583 --> 34:22.500
When they go, suddenly you got
all this important shit to say to 'em.

34:23.125 --> 34:26.208
Or not important shit. You just want to...

34:27.583 --> 34:29.875
Just want to tell 'em stuff.

35:02.000 --> 35:03.083
Hi.

35:28.583 --> 35:30.042
[students chattering]

35:30.042 --> 35:32.708
- [Laci] Look at Nate. Such a dork.
- [Megan] Aw, Nate.

35:32.708 --> 35:36.667
[Brittany] Oh, my God. What is that?
Are you dancing?

35:36.667 --> 35:40.708
Hey, don't hate on my moves. Okay?
I was killin' that.

35:40.708 --> 35:42.792
Oh, Doris, come here.

35:45.542 --> 35:46.583
- [Laci] Hey, girl.
- [Doris] Hey.

35:46.583 --> 35:49.958
- These are from your party.
- That shit was off the chain.

35:49.958 --> 35:54.042
Oh, really? Thanks. I had fun too.

35:54.042 --> 35:57.167
Hey, so my birthday is this weekend.

35:57.167 --> 35:59.375
Could we maybe have
another party at your house?

36:00.583 --> 36:03.583
Well, my mom won't be home, so...

36:03.583 --> 36:06.083
- Yeah, definitely.
- Amazing.

36:06.083 --> 36:07.375
Wait, do you smoke weed?

36:07.375 --> 36:08.625
Oh...

36:09.333 --> 36:15.333
Not right now.
But I'm thinking about starting soon.

36:19.083 --> 36:20.208
Yeah, I do.

36:20.208 --> 36:21.292
[Brittany] Cool.

36:21.292 --> 36:22.833
[Brittany] Oh, my God.

36:22.833 --> 36:24.375
[upbeat music]

36:27.458 --> 36:29.042
Oh, my God.

36:30.458 --> 36:32.458
[Megan] Do we need to, like,
take you to the hospital?

36:33.667 --> 36:36.583
Oh, guess who texted me last night?

36:36.583 --> 36:38.167
Oh, my God. Aaron Miller?

36:38.167 --> 36:40.250
- [Brittany] Correct.
- [Doris] Who?

36:40.250 --> 36:41.833
You don't know Aaron Miller?

36:41.833 --> 36:44.167
- No.
- Do you not, like, live in this town?

36:44.625 --> 36:46.125
[Brittany] He's a few years older than us.

36:46.125 --> 36:48.125
He's so hot.

36:48.125 --> 36:50.250
- Ew.
- Ew.

36:50.250 --> 36:52.500
He is, he is.

36:52.500 --> 36:55.042
We dated for almost a year, but...

36:56.083 --> 36:58.917
he broke it off last month
because he said, I'm, like...

37:00.583 --> 37:01.958
like, immature.

37:02.417 --> 37:05.833
Oh, um... I'm sorry.

37:06.583 --> 37:09.958
I feel like only a really immature person
would be callous enough

37:09.958 --> 37:11.458
to call someone else immature.

37:13.500 --> 37:14.750
Holy shit.

37:15.958 --> 37:17.583
You're so right.

37:18.083 --> 37:22.417
Wow. I've, like, never
thought about it like that.

37:23.250 --> 37:26.792
Yeah, that was, like,
some deep shit, Doris.

37:26.792 --> 37:28.750
Ooh, Deep Doris.

37:31.000 --> 37:35.125
Okay. Well, Deep Doris,
you just earned yourself a keg stand.

37:35.125 --> 37:36.292
What?

37:36.292 --> 37:38.625
- You don't know what a keg stand is?
- No.

37:38.625 --> 37:41.083
Oh, my God, you're like an alien.

37:41.083 --> 37:44.583
[Brittany] Dude, you asked me
if cheese was a vegetable

37:44.583 --> 37:46.625
- and you're calling her an alien?
- No!

37:46.625 --> 37:48.792
No, that was, like, five years ago.

37:48.792 --> 37:51.292
- That was not five years ago.
- Yes, it was.

37:51.292 --> 37:53.125
- More like months.
- It was five...

37:57.000 --> 37:59.042
So, this is going to be so much fun.

37:59.042 --> 38:02.583
Just put your hands right here...
and trust them.

38:03.083 --> 38:04.833
It'll be fun, it'll be fun, it'll be fun.

38:05.292 --> 38:06.333
[Doris] Oh, my God!

38:08.250 --> 38:10.958
[all] One, two, three...

38:39.333 --> 38:40.458
[Brittany] What?

38:44.875 --> 38:46.375
What?

38:46.375 --> 38:51.167
What the fuck is he doing?
Run, you dumbass!

38:52.833 --> 38:55.917
- Okay. Guess what I heard?
- What?

38:55.917 --> 38:57.417
Nate has a crush on Doris.

38:57.417 --> 38:59.375
What? Yeah, right.

38:59.375 --> 39:01.625
- No way.
- Wait. Where'd you hear that?

39:01.625 --> 39:04.000
[Brittany] Aw, that's so hot.

39:04.000 --> 39:07.167
The two of you together,
I would die of horniness.

39:07.167 --> 39:09.667
- But who told you that?
- Do you like him?

39:09.667 --> 39:11.542
I don't know.

39:11.542 --> 39:14.292
Oh, if you do, I can, like,
totally make it happen.

39:14.292 --> 39:19.250
Yeah. I mean, he's not all, like,
deep and quiet or whatever like you are,

39:19.250 --> 39:22.083
but he's a little panty melter, right?

39:22.958 --> 39:25.083
I mean, he's sort of cute.

39:25.583 --> 39:26.917
Oh, my God.

39:26.917 --> 39:28.250
- She loves him.
- She loves him.

39:28.250 --> 39:29.792
You love him.

39:31.125 --> 39:34.292
- You should go to prom with him.
- What? Okay, yeah.

39:34.292 --> 39:36.708
Now that that's out there,
you're going with him.

39:36.708 --> 39:38.667
I'm sorry. You're going. You have to.

39:38.667 --> 39:42.875
Yeah, but don't get her hopes up because
he might not, like, actually be into her.

39:44.417 --> 39:45.625
Ew.

39:45.625 --> 39:48.625
You sound really jealous, and it's boring.

39:48.625 --> 39:50.042
So boring.

39:52.042 --> 39:53.917
[Laci] Can I put some gel in your hair?

39:53.917 --> 39:56.958
Oh, I hate my hair.
I don't know what to do with it.

39:56.958 --> 39:58.875
You should straighten that shit.

39:58.875 --> 40:01.208
I would, like, kill myself
if I had curly hair.

40:01.208 --> 40:03.292
Well, I wish you had curly hair.

40:04.583 --> 40:06.667
Where's your gel? I want to mess with it.

40:06.667 --> 40:09.500
My mom might have some
in the bathroom closet.

